            "body": "If vim doesn't behave differently, the problem you're encountering is probably a netrw issue and not a neovim issue. I think you should contact [netrw's author](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a270c33b3a49d7a47b1bb6e6b9eb2073d98e0602/runtime/autoload/netrwSettings.vim#L3) as Neovim doesn't maintain its own runtime files, it just copies them from Vim.",
